=Analyze this social media post for Acme National Bank.

Post ID: {{ $json.id }}
Platform: {{ $json.platform }}
Author: {{ $json.author_name }} (@{{ $json.author_handle }})
Content: {{ $json.content }}
Likes: {{ $json.likes }} | Shares: {{ $json.shares }} | Comments: {{ $json.comments_count }}

STEP 1: Call lookupCustomerByHandle with handle "{{ $json.author_handle }}" to check if this is a bank customer.
STEP 2: Call getActiveIncidents to check for known issues.
STEP 3: Based on the tool results, respond with ONLY a JSON object (no markdown, no explanation) with these exact fields:
{
  "is_banking_related": "yes" or "no",
  "sentiment": "positive" or "neutral" or "negative" or "critical",
  "issue_category": "Service Outage" or "Security Concern" or "Fee Complaint" or "App Bug" or "Fraud Report" or "Other",
  "confidence_score": "0.92",
  "key_topics": "topic1, topic2",
  "suggested_response": "your empathetic public reply for negative/critical posts, brief thanks for positive, No response needed for neutral",
  "escalation_target": "security_team" or "pr_team" or "customer_support" or "no_escalation"
}

Escalation rules: security/fraud/phishing -> security_team, high-engagement negative (>100 likes or >50 shares) -> pr_team, service complaints from identified customers -> customer_support, positive/neutral -> no_escalation. Platinum/private banking customers with complaints always escalate to customer_support.

